heading: whitewater rests
subheading: the federal grand jury investigating financial and legal transactions in the arkansas background of clinton and wife hillary completed its work tuesday, two days early. the panel disbanded after two years of sifting evidence for ken starr, and closed shop with just one indictment -- that of former clinton associate susan mcdougal. the empanelment of another grand jury is possible, but there's been no decision, starr's office said.
author: wired staff
